II: Excerpt from NKVD Operational Order 00447 -- tAppendix III: Operational Order No. 00486 -- tChronology -- tSelected Glossary of Names, Places, and Institutions -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aRoughly ten million children were victims of political repression in the Soviet Union during the Stalinist era, the sons and daughters of peasants, workers, scientists, physicians, and political leaders considered by the regime to be dangerous to the political order. Ten grown victims, who as children suffered banishment, starvation, disease, anti-Semitism, and trauma resulting from their parents' condemnation and arrest, now freely share their stories.  The result is a powerful and moving oral history that will profoundly deepen the reader's understanding of life in the U.S.S.R. under the despotic reign of Joseph Stalin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCommunismxSocial aspectszSoviet Union. 0aPolitical prisonerszSoviet UnionvBiography. 0aPolitical prisonerszSoviet UnionvInterviews. 0aPolitical purgeszSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zSoviet Union. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210736423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300210736.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles